# --- API base (`src/config/env.ts`) ---
# If you set EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL, the app uses it for ALL API calls (including images under /uploads).
# If you omit it or leave it commented, the app uses https://api.sembuzz.com (same as production).
#
# Expo Go + "Network Error" / AxiosError almost always means: nothing is listening at this URL.
# Fix ONE of:
#   (A) Start the backend: `cd ../backend && npm run start:dev` (listens on :3000), then restart Expo.
#   (B) Comment out EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL below to point Expo Go at production API while you only work on UI.
#
# Local backend examples (pick one):
#   iOS Simulator on Mac:     http://localhost:3000
#   Android emulator:         http://10.0.2.2:3000
#   Physical phone (Expo Go): http://YOUR_MAC_LAN_IP:3000  (not "localhost" — that is the phone itself)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# If EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL is localhost but you load **production** news (same DB or prod API data),
# images are on the VPS — set this so /uploads/* resolves to production:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ASSET_BASE_URL=https://api.sembuzz.com

# Frontend base for opening web routes from the app (register, legal, etc.)
EXPO_PUBLIC_FRONTEND_URL=https://sembuzz.com
